think that in order

00:32:10.260 --> 00:32:14.160
to make sure that we
can obtain the quality,

00:32:14.160 --> 00:32:17.580
we pay a lot of
attention to details

00:32:17.580 --> 00:32:21.010
by using scientific methods.

00:32:21.010 --> 00:32:25.680
For example, when it comes
to the milling process, which

00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:29.220
is the first stage
that we do at Kavalan,

00:32:29.220 --> 00:32:38.300
where you use mills to
break the multi barley into

00:32:38.300 --> 00:32:44.190
define the course and the
flour, the three portions.

00:32:44.190 --> 00:32:46.800
We always make sure that
our quality control people,

00:32:46.800 --> 00:32:50.820
they do the this
size determination

00:32:50.820 --> 00:32:52.770
work on a daily
basis to make sure

00:32:52.770 --> 00:32:56.910
that this is at a
so-called golden ratio

00:32:56.910 --> 00:32:59.470
of our golden ratio.

00:32:59.470 --> 00:33:02.640
So that for the next
stage of our mashing,

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:07.740
we manage to extract the
maximum amount of starch

00:33:07.740 --> 00:33:13.740
into glucose by the natural
conversion of internal enzymes

00:33:13.740 --> 00:33:15.240
of the malted barley.

00:33:15.240 --> 00:33:17.910
And this is, once
again achieved by using

00:33:17.910 --> 00:33:21.720
very precise temperature
control equipment

00:33:21.720 --> 00:33:24.030
that we have at the distillery.

00:33:24.030 --> 00:33:29.010
So that during the mashing
process from the first water,

00:33:29.010 --> 00:33:33.570
which is always 63.5
degrees Celsius, and then

00:33:33.570 --> 00:33:37.980
the second water to be 85,
and a third one to be 90.

00:33:37.980 --> 00:33:42.460
And then followed
by the fermentation,

00:33:42.460 --> 00:33:47.040
where we also use the
so-called jacketed vessel,

00:33:47.040 --> 00:33:54.810
so that we can run cold water
in the outside of the jacket

00:33:54.810 --> 00:33:58.080
to control the temperature
during the fermentation

00:33:58.080 --> 00:33:58.980
process.

00:33:58.980 --> 00:34:02.520
Because this is,
once again, it will

00:34:02.520 --> 00:34:06.180
affect the quality
of your wash, which

00:34:06.180 --> 00:34:13.400
is the alcoholic, which
is also called beer,

00:34:13.400 --> 00:34:17.300
can have a very high
content of alcohol.

00:34:17.300 --> 00:34:21.030
Also very fruity, very
complex, the note.

00:34:21.030 --> 00:34:25.409
So these are all just
some of these examples

00:34:25.409 --> 00:34:31.620
of what we do to in order to
obtain quality in our product

00:34:31.620 --> 00:34:34.830
by using scientific method.

00:34:34.830 --> 00:34:39.270
And also when it comes
to the final stage,

00:34:39.270 --> 00:34:45.570
we also use our
GCMS and also HPLC,

00:34:45.570 --> 00:34:49.480
all these high tech
chemical analysis

00:34:49.480 --> 00:34:54.659
to determine whether we have
the right amount of wood related

00:34:54.659 --> 00:35:01.290
flavors, the right amount
of oxidized compounds

00:35:01.290 --> 00:35:05.340
in order to contribute
to your good mouth feel,

00:35:05.340 --> 00:35:09.120
and also the good fragrance
when you nose the whisky.

00:35:09.120 --> 00:35:15.240
So that's what we do at Kavalan
in terms of scientific methods.

